The paper describes a new mobile architecture for improving performance on multiple tasks and benchmarks, including object detection and semantic segmentation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses efficient ways of applying these mobile models, which could fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning techniques and convolutional neural networks also suggests that the paper could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its performance on various datasets, which could fall under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
